# Knotwork — the lead, rebuilt from the CIRCUIT out. The failure before:
# sync at +3 barely engages (the slave resets a sliver early, so you
# just hear a minor-third dyad on every note) and ring at ratio 1.19
# dumps a 0.19f subharmonic growl. All gone.
# The voice now IS the ladder: resonance 2.2 with key_track 1.0 makes
# the filter's own whistle a TUNED PARTIAL that follows the melody —
# a component no acoustic instrument owns, native to this circuit.
# Under it: saw + octave pulse (harmonic-safe reinforcement), ring at
# +12 whose products land on f and 3f — harmonic sheen, not clang.
# The filter env (+0.6 oct, 120 ms attack) glides the whistle up INTO
# place after each note lands; the slow filter LFO makes it breathe.
waveform 2
osc2_wave 1
osc2_pitch 12
osc2_level 0.3
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 4
sub 0
circuit 0
key_track 1.0
osc_fm 0
sync 0
ring 0.12
glide 0
pulse_width 0.4
attack 0.03
decay 0.5
sustain 0.8
release 0.4
filter_env 0.6
filter_attack 0.12
filter_decay 0.6
filter_sustain 0.6
filter_release 0.35
cutoff 1600
resonance 2.2
drive 2.0
saturation 1.0
hpf 90
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0
fuzz 0
spring 0.12
lfo_rate 0.6
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0.08
lfo_pwm 0.12
